OL,6,FBut in Soweto, once the home of the
OL,7,Fanti-apartheid movement, we are
OL,8,Freminded that despite the distance
OL,9,Fleft towards what most would call
OL,10,F'liberation', the country has
OL,11,Ftravelled a long way since the ANC
OL,12,Fcame to power.
OL,14,FThe perspective is shared by the
OL,15,FMolefes family who we first met in
OL,16,F2010 as the football World Cup was
OL,17,Fbeing opened in a stadium a few
OL,18,Fminutes drive from their home.
