OL,6,FTheir neighbourhood felt energised
OL,7,Fthat day as South Africans welcomed
OL,8,Fthe world.
OL,10,FBut, Nothemba, a school teacher, and
OL,11,Fher husband Mandla, a municipal
OL,12,Fworker, worried about the longer term:
OL,13,FWhat direction would the country go in
OL,14,Fonce the party ended and the vuvuzelas
OL,15,Fstopped playing? Would this become the
OL,16,Fsociety they had been promised, where
OL,17,Ftheir children would be allowed to
OL,18,Fthrive?
